Q: Vue3 + nested components from PHP template A: <p>Registering <code>othercomponent</code> from inside testComponent won’t make it available to the already-compiled slot content,
Register them globally on <code>app.js</code></p>
<pre><code>import { createApp } from &quot;vue/dist/vue.esm-bundler&quot;;
import TestComponent from &quot;./components/testComponent.vue&quot;;
import OtherComponent from &quot;./components/otherComponent.vue&quot;;

createApp({})
  .component(&quot;testcomponent&quot;, TestComponent)
  .component(&quot;othercomponent&quot;, OtherComponent)
  .mount(&quot;#vueApp&quot;);
</code></pre>
<p>Then you can just use in rendered template</p>
<pre><code>&lt;div id=&quot;vueApp&quot;&gt;
  &lt;testcomponent&gt;
    &lt;othercomponent&gt;&lt;/othercomponent&gt;
  &lt;/testcomponent&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

</code></pre>
